### Coral reefs
- corals themselves are tiny animals thich belong to the scientific group called cnidaria
- are sessile animals
- feed by reaching out with their tentacles to catch prey
	- mainly small fish and plantonic animals
- corals live in colonies consisting of many other corals 
- each induvidual coral is called a polyp

- virtually all reef dwelling corals have a symbiotic relationship with an algea called zooxanthellea
	- plant like algea live inside the coral polyp and perform photosynthesis giving the coral oxygen
	- zooxanthellea also give the coral their vibrant colors[^1]
- coral provide homes for:
	- mollusk, sea slugs, nubranchs, oysters, clams, crustasteans, cniderms, sea fans, sharks, etc.
- coral reefs provide buffers against storms
